<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/24312335-jennieblakey"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/24312335-jennieblakey">Jennieblakey</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    Dolores knew the accident wasn't her fault, but she carried the guilt anyway. Who wouldn't? When she found out that Nichole lied, it allowed her to fi<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    Dolores knew the accident wasn't her fault, but she carried the guilt anyway. Who wouldn't? When she found out that Nichole lied, it allowed her to finally be honest with herself and accept that because she knew Nichole lied, she, herself, couldn't have been at fault. Even though the rest of the town now believed her to be guilty, falsely, and hence shunned her, the true burden Dolores had carried was her self-imposed guilt. The freedom of that burden also allowed her to feel something of her own for the first time in who knows how long. The fact that even Abbott, who seemingly knew everything intuitively and profoundly since his stroke, could no longer feel sure he knew the truth of the accident, also set Dolores free of her burden because this truth was hers. <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
