<div id="review_460139208" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/460139208" />
    <a title="George K. Ilsley" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4003368-george-k-ilsley"><img alt="George K. Ilsley" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442467989p2/4003368.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/460139208?book_show_action=true">Nov 20, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="George K. Ilsley" class="user" itemprop="url" name="George K. Ilsley" href="/user/show/4003368-george-k-ilsley">George K. Ilsley</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780676970944" href="/book/show/365275.The_Sweet_Hereafter">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4003368-george-k-ilsley?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer460139208" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3876088422345740809">This is my first sweet taste of the Russell Banks experience. Well, it&apos;s a solid and evocative exposure that made this reader feel like he had spent a long time in the town getting to know the people. Insightful perspectives from the viewpoint of several characters, all presented in the form of smooth, seemingly effortless writing. Brilliant. If all his novels are like this I can see what the fuss is about.<br/>4.5 stars. </span>
  <span id="freeText3876088422345740809" style="display:none">This is my first sweet taste of the Russell Banks experience. Well, it's a solid and evocative exposure that made this reader feel like he had spent a long time in the town getting to know the people. Insightful perspectives from the viewpoint of several characters, all presented in the form of smooth, seemingly effortless writing. Brilliant. If all his novels are like this I can see what the fuss is about.<br />4.5 stars. </span>
