<div id="review_4204303071" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4204303071" />
    <a title="Anne Caverhill" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17237704-anne-caverhill"><img alt="Anne Caverhill" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4204303071?book_show_action=true">Aug 28, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anne Caverhill" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anne Caverhill" href="/user/show/17237704-anne-caverhill">Anne Caverhill</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17237704-anne-caverhill?shelf=books-read-in-2021">books-read-in-2021</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4204303071" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13190549185290298441">This book was as gratifying to read now as it was 30 years ago when I first picked it up. On its face, it’s about an unspeakable tragedy, a small misfit of a town losing 14 children in a bus accident. That incident is pervasive and the overall theme of the chapters, yet the hardcore stories are the various characters from the town, including the brilliant 14 year old wielding powerful control over her new life in a wheel chair. <br/>The writing will make you gasp with its sharp simplicity of pain and</span>
  <span id="freeText13190549185290298441" style="display:none">This book was as gratifying to read now as it was 30 years ago when I first picked it up. On its face, it’s about an unspeakable tragedy, a small misfit of a town losing 14 children in a bus accident. That incident is pervasive and the overall theme of the chapters, yet the hardcore stories are the various characters from the town, including the brilliant 14 year old wielding powerful control over her new life in a wheel chair. <br />The writing will make you gasp with its sharp simplicity of pain and the terror of life after burying the bodies of small children. Still one of my favourite stories and brilliantly conveyed in film.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13190549185290298441" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


