        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3957146130" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15351829034823827758">A bus accident that causes the death of 14 children in a small town of Sam Dent and the narratives of the various people in the town forms the entire book. What Russell Banks gets right is the voice of a 50 (ish) year old woman. He gets maybe a 35 year old man&apos;s right too. And where he doesn&apos;t quite is that of a 14 year old girl. I felt that he was unable to shake off his sane, clear narrative and get fully into the shoes of a young girl. So despite the many attempted voices, it felt like one. </span>
  <span id="freeText15351829034823827758" style="display:none">A bus accident that causes the death of 14 children in a small town of Sam Dent and the narratives of the various people in the town forms the entire book. What Russell Banks gets right is the voice of a 50 (ish) year old woman. He gets maybe a 35 year old man's right too. And where he doesn't quite is that of a 14 year old girl. I felt that he was unable to shake off his sane, clear narrative and get fully into the shoes of a young girl. So despite the many attempted voices, it felt like one. </span>
