<div id="review_1580364452" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1580364452" />
    <a title="CK" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7013021-ck"><img alt="CK" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1641054865p2/7013021.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1580364452?book_show_action=true">Mar 15, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="CK" class="user" itemprop="url" name="CK" href="/user/show/7013021-ck">CK</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780060923242" href="/book/show/273499.The_Sweet_Hereafter">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7013021-ck?shelf=owned">owned</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1580364452" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer273576883209485920">At first I did not like this book, only because it is sort of misleading in the beginning. Despite the crash, the book seemed innocent enough until the perspective changes and suddenly sexual affairs, drugs, and rape are discussed without any warning. Once you realize that this book, even though it&apos;s central focus is on a crash and how it affects a town, covers a broad selection of topics you will start to enjoy it. The characters were very interesting and made the story. Also I&apos;m always a sucke</span>
  <span id="freeText273576883209485920" style="display:none">At first I did not like this book, only because it is sort of misleading in the beginning. Despite the crash, the book seemed innocent enough until the perspective changes and suddenly sexual affairs, drugs, and rape are discussed without any warning. Once you realize that this book, even though it's central focus is on a crash and how it affects a town, covers a broad selection of topics you will start to enjoy it. The characters were very interesting and made the story. Also I'm always a sucker for when the author uses the title of the book within the text.</span>
  <a data-text-id="273576883209485920" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

